Steps of implementation:
a)	CRUD routes – GET return JSON (e-2-e test)
b)	Add middleware functionality (TDD – unit tests) : Validation .
c)	Error handling – logging 
d)	Swagger endpoints.
e)	Save to Database – Mongo 
f)	Add middleware functionality (TDD – unit tests) : which uses callbacks, promises and async await .
g)	Authenticate – add bearer token which allows someone to /POST to it (TDD’d)
h)	Docker-ise. 
i)	Deploy
j)	Stretch: Produce to kafka, consumer posts then save these to mongo.
